===Etymology===
Fusion of {{etyl|enm}} {{term|redden||to deliver from, rid, clear|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|hreddan||to deliver, rescue, free from, take away|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|hradjaną||to save, deliver|lang=gem-pro}}) and {{enm}} {{term|ridden||to clear away, remove obstructions|lang=enm}} (from {{ang}} {{term|gehryddan|ġeryddan|to clear land|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|riudijaną||to clear|lang=gem-pro}}). Akin to {{etyl|ofs|-}} {{term|hredda||to save|lang=ofs}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|retten||to save, deliver|lang=de}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|ryðja||to clear, empty|lang=non}}, {{non}} {{term|hróðja|hrōðja|to clear, strip|lang=non}}. More at [[redd]].

